<section id="Editing_MAC_Address_Pool_Permissions">
	<title>Editing MAC Address Pool Permissions</title>
        <para>
		 After a MAC address pool has been created, you can edit its user permissions. The user permissions control which data centers can use the MAC address pool. See <xref linkend="sect-Roles" /> for more information on adding new user permissions. 
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>Editing MAC Address Pool Permissions</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				On the header bar, click the <guilabel>Configure</guilabel> button to open the <guilabel>Configure</guilabel> window.
			</para>
		</step>
                <step>
			<para>
				Click the <guilabel>MAC Address Pools</guilabel> tab.
			</para>
		</step>
                <step>
			<para>
				Select the required MAC address pool.
			</para>
		</step>
                <step>
                    <para>
                        Edit the user permissions for the MAC address pool:
                    </para>
                    <stepalternatives>
				<step>
                                    <para>To add user permissions to a MAC address pool:</para>
                                    <substeps>
                                        <step>
                                            <para>
                                                Click <guilabel>Add</guilabel> in the user permissions pane at the bottom of the <guilabel>Configure</guilabel> window.
                                                </para>
                                            </step>
                                            <step>
                                                <para>
                                                    Search for and select the required users.
                                                    </para>
                                                </step>
						<step>
                                                <para>
                                                    Select the required role from the <guilabel>Role to Assign</guilabel> drop-down list.
                                                    </para>
                                                </step>
                                                <step>
                                                    <para> 
                                          Click <guilabel>OK</guilabel> to add the user permissions. 
                                        </para>
                                                    </step>
                                        </substeps>
                                </step>
                                <step>
                        <para>To remove user permissions from a MAC address pool:</para>
                        <substeps>
                            <step>
                                <para>
                                    Select the user permission to be removed in the user permissions pane at the bottom of the <guilabel>Configure</guilabel> window.
                                    </para>
                                </step>
                                <step>
                                    <para>
                                        Click <guilabel>Remove</guilabel> to remove the user permissions.
                                        </para>
                                    </step>
                            </substeps>
                    </step>
                    </stepalternatives>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>
